{"parentUuid":"f7d7c212-7fb3-4e69-bbda-e018d46b67a7","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HgUv2GWpHKzLag3rk6axew","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying they haven't cloned a repo or initialized git at all - they just opened a folder in VS Code and git isn't set up yet. They need to either:\n1. Initialize a new git repo (`git init`)\n2. Or connect to an existing remote repo\n\nLet me explain the basic flow for setting up git in VS Code for the first time.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":268,"cache_read_input_tokens":15610,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":268},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZYfWBQUFJ2nTR9QqEDCZ","type":"assistant","uuid":"8623e453-73f9-4f1f-a266-5ec463f60d4d","timestamp":"2026-03-30T04:52:04.262Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"/home/imyo","sessionId":"936b037b-67bf-4edc-8dd3-deb250b820c0","version":"2.1.87","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
{"parentUuid":"8623e453-73f9-4f1f-a266-5ec463f60d4d","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HgUv2GWpHKzLag3rk6axew","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes! You need to initialize git first. Here are the two common scenarios:\n\n**Option 1: You have existing code locally (no repo yet)**\n\n```bash\ngit init\ngit add .\ngit commit -m \"first commit\"\ngit remote add origin <your-repo-url>\ngit push -u origin main\n```\n\n**Option 2: You want to clone an existing repo from GitHub**\n\n```bash\ngit clone <your-repo-url>\n```\n\nThen open that cloned folder in VS Code.\n\n---\n\n**In VS Code UI (no terminal needed):**\n\n1. Open the **Source Control** panel (Ctrl+Shift+G)\n2. Click **\"Initialize Repository\"** — this runs `git init` for you\n3. Stage and commit your files\n4. Click **\"Publish Branch\"** — VS Code will ask you to connect to GitHub\n\n---\n\nWhich situation are you in?\n- **New project** with code already on your computer → Option 1 (or VS Code UI)\n- **Existing repo** on GitHub you want to work on → Option 2 (clone)"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":268,"cache_read_input_tokens":15610,"output_tokens":346,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":268,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZYfWBQUFJ2nTR9QqEDCZ","type":"assistant","uuid":"bd4e7dbd-db59-4627-9e4a-957873889af1","timestamp":"2026-03-30T04:52:08.461Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"/home/imyo","sessionId":"936b037b-67bf-4edc-8dd3-deb250b820c0","version":"2.1.87","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
